So Mr. Rutherford (that great champion for Presbytery) the Apostle (saith he) sheweth what was their duty as Christians convened together in a Church-way: the Apostle doth not command one christian, but the Church gathered together in the name of the Lord Jesus to cast himout;


                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  . we apply it (saith he) to the casting of scandalous persons out of the Church, as leaven was to be put out of the Houses of all who were to eat the Passover. But.
